@startuml component
title jwt-for-beginners — Component Architecture

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor Client

package "src/" {
  [server.js\n(entrypoint)] as server
  [createApp\n(composition root)] as app
  package "routes" {
    [auth router\n/register, /login]
    [me router\n/me]
  }
  package "middleware" {
    [requireAuth\n(Bearer + verify + lookup)] as auth
  }
  package "services" {
    [UserStore\n(in-memory, bcrypt-hashed)] as store
    [JwtService\n(sign + verify)] as jwts
    [loadConfig\n(zod-validated env)] as cfg
  }
}

Client --> app : HTTP
app --> auth : depends (for /me)
[auth router\n/register, /login] --> store : add / verifyPassword
[auth router\n/register, /login] --> jwts : sign
auth --> jwts : verify
auth --> store : findById
server --> cfg : loadConfig()
server --> app : createApp({config})

note bottom of store
  bcrypt.hash on add (rounds from config).
  verifyPassword runs even when name is
  missing — uniform timing avoids
  username-enumeration via response time.
end note

note right of auth
  Returns 401 with distinct reasons:
   - missing header
   - token expired / invalid
   - user no longer exists
end note
@enduml
